{
  "url": "https://www.hymnal.net/en/hymn/h/1144",
  "title": "In the Word of old, we are clearly told",
  "verses": [
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "In the Word of old, we are clearly told,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "In His image God created man."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "To express His worth, to subdue the earth,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Have dominion and fulfill His plan."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "1"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Image, image,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "In His image He created man."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Image, image,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "For dominion, to fulfill His Plan."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "chorus"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Yet no rules He gave, no instructions, save:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "“Every tree shall be to thee for meat.”"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "But one tree, He said, surely makes you dead;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Fruit of knowledge isn’t good to eat."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "2"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Knowledge, knowledge,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Fruit of knowledge wasn’t meant for meat."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Knowledge, knowledge,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Fruit of knowledge isn’t good to eat."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "chorus"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Midst the garden fair, see the life tree there—"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "God Himself the tree of life does show."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "But the enemy, somehow subtly"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Tempted man the other tree to know."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "3"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Fallen, fallen,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Man has eaten of the deadly tree."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Fallen, fallen,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Man requires a full recovery."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "chorus"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Then came Jesus Christ as the tree of life,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Satisfying all that God required."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "He redeemed the earth, giving man new birth,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "And became the food that man desired."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "4"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Jesus, Jesus,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Jesus Christ is really good to eat."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Jesus, Jesus,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "He is real drink and real meat."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "chorus"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Jesus ne’er designed e’er to feed our mind;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "All good knowledge only puffeth up."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "But He came, He said, as a feast instead,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Not to analyze, but only sup."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "5"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Take Him, take Him,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Wholly satisfying, glorious."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Take Him, take Him,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Jesus is the tree of life to us."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "chorus"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "As we eat the Lord, growth He does afford,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Life and numbers soon will be increased."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "We must clearly see God’s recovery—"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Christ is not religion, but a feast."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "6"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Eat Him, eat Him,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Christ as life is all the food we need."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Eat Him, eat Him,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "He who eateth Him shall live indeed."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "chorus"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Eating is the way to live Christ today,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Of the eating there should be no lack."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "As the churches eat, they become complete,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Eating Christ will bring the Bridegroom back."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "7"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Eating, eating,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Of our eating there must be no lack."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Eating, eating,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Eating Christ will bring the Bridegroom back."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "chorus"
    }
  ],
